      "content": "The Civil Rights Movement in the US, primarily from the 1950s to the 1960s, was a pivotal struggle against systemic racism and segregation. Key events include the 1954 Brown v. Board of Education Supreme Court decision, which declared segregation in public schools unconstitutional, and the 1963 March on Washington, where Martin Luther King Jr. delivered his iconic \"I Have a Dream\" speech. The Civil Rights Act of 1964 and the Voting Rights Act of 1965 were landmark legislations that outlawed discrimination and protected voting rights. The movement was driven by African Americans and their allies, who fought for equality and justice, ultimately leading to significant social and political changes.",
